&lt;p&gt;ÊàëÂ∞ùËØï‰∫Ü&lt;span class=&#34;exturl&#34; data-url=&#34;aHR0cHM6Ly9wdmUucHJveG1veC5jb20vcHZlLWRvY3MvY2hhcHRlci1xbS5odG1s&#34;&gt;ÂÆòÊñπÊñáÊ°£&lt;/span&gt;‰∏≠ Host Device Passthrough ÈÉ®ÂàÜÁöÑÊñπÊ≥ïÔºö&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;note information&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For both methods you need to &lt;span class=&#34;exturl&#34; data-url=&#34;aHR0cHM6Ly9wdmUucHJveG1veC5jb20vcHZlLWRvY3MvY2hhcHRlci1xbS5odG1sI3FtX3BjaV9wYXNzdGhyb3VnaF91cGRhdGVfaW5pdHJhbWZz&#34;&gt;update the initramfs&lt;/span&gt; again and reboot after that.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should this not work, you might need to set a soft dependency to load the gpu modules before loading &lt;em&gt;vfio-pci&lt;/em&gt;. This can be done with the &lt;em&gt;softdep&lt;/em&gt; flag, see also the manpages on &lt;em&gt;modprobe.d&lt;/em&gt; for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For example, if you are using drivers named  &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;some-module&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;  :&lt;/p&gt;
